# Fork upstream merge

Use branch `chore/merge-upstream-*` from `main`. Full cycle: `delivery-cycle.mdc`.

## Checklist

1. `git fetch upstream` — never commit on `upstream-main`
2. Resolve hot files: `purchase.py`, `tariff_purchase.py`, `start.py`, `inline.py`, `texts.py`, `balance/main.py`, `bot.py`
3. **Keep overlay:** `app/plugins/**`, `app/localization/locales/fa.json`, `PRICE_DISPLAY_*` in config
4. `balance/main.py` conflicts: keep C2C (and other) hooks **and** upstream provider branches
5. Post-merge: `import main`, Alembic at head, user smoke — one fa path, price display, C2C if enabled
6. Merge to `dev-local` → `main` only after user approval

## Rollback

`git revert` on merge commit — not `reset --hard` on shared branches.
